        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 5:02PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Tallassee. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Tuskegee, Tallassee, Milstead, Shorter, Franklin, Liverpool,
Victoryland, Liberty City, Reeves Airport, Tallapoosa City, Yates
Dam, and Yates Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
